🎯 🔥 MASTER PROMPT — SAME FLOW, MULTIPLE UI REPRESENTATIONS
🧠 Objective

Build a real-time fintech dashboard UI system where a single transaction flow pipeline is represented across multiple UI components simultaneously, all driven by the same data source.

🔗 CORE CONCEPT (VERY IMPORTANT)

There is ONE event flow:

Dispatcher → Scenario → Payload → Connect → Event Store

This flow must be visualized in different UI components, but all must stay perfectly synchronized using shared state.

🧩 REQUIRED UI COMPONENTS
1. 🧱 Architecture Diagram (System View)
Show pipeline as connected nodes:
Dispatcher (green)
Scenario (blue)
Payload (red)
Connect (amber vertical)
Add:
Kafka topic nodes below
Event Store (capsule shape) at bottom
Show:
Success / error counts per node
Include:
Animated flow between nodes
2. 📊 Live Event Stream (Transaction View)
Each transaction is a row
Show:
Transaction ID (GBM-XXXXX)
Type (FX_TRADE, etc.)
Pipeline progress (step-by-step)
Highlight:
Active stage (blue)
Completed (green)
Failed (red)
3. 🚨 Incident Monitor (Error View)
Right-side panel
Show only failed transactions
Each card includes:
Transaction ID
Failed stage (source)
Timestamp
Error message
LIFO order (latest first)
4. 🧾 Kafka Log Panel (System Trace)
Bottom panel (dark theme)
Show logs like:
[HH:MM:SS] INGEST >> [TX_ID] Topic: T24.RAW | Type: FX_TRADE
Auto-scroll enabled
5. 📊 Header Metrics
Total Volume
Health %
Active Issues
🧠 SHARED DATA MODEL (MANDATORY)

All components must use the SAME data:

type Transaction = {
  id: string;
  type: string;
  stage: "DISPATCHER" | "SCENARIO" | "PAYLOAD" | "CONNECT";
  status: "PROCESSING" | "SUCCESS" | "ERROR";
  timestamp: number;
  error?: string;
};
🔄 DATA FLOW (CRITICAL)

Simulate or integrate real-time updates:

Event Source → State Store → All Components Update
⚙️ STATE MANAGEMENT

Use a centralized state:

transactions[]
logs[]
incidents[]
metrics{}

Each UI component must derive data from this shared state, not separate logic.

🔁 SYNCHRONIZATION RULE

When a transaction updates:

Diagram updates metrics
Event stream updates row
Incident panel updates (if error)
Logs panel appends entry

👉 All at the same time

⚡ BEHAVIOR
Transactions move step-by-step across pipeline
Random failures occur (~10%)
Logs generated on each step
Incident created on failure
